comment: * Provides access to telephony configuration values that are carrier-specific.

variables.name: EXTRA_SLOT_INDEX
variables.comment:
* Extra included in {@link #ACTION_CARRIER_CONFIG_CHANGED} to indicate the slot index that the
     * broadcast is for.

variables.name: EXTRA_REBROADCAST_ON_UNLOCK
variables.comment:
* {@link #ACTION_CARRIER_CONFIG_CHANGED} is broadcast once on device bootup and then again when
     * the device is unlocked. Direct-Boot-aware applications may use the first broadcast as an
     * early signal that the carrier config has been loaded, but other applications will only
     * receive the second broadcast, when the device is unlocked.
     *
     * This extra is included in {@link #ACTION_CARRIER_CONFIG_CHANGED} to indicate whether this is
     * a rebroadcast on unlock.

variables.name: EXTRA_SUBSCRIPTION_INDEX
variables.comment:
* Optional extra included in {@link #ACTION_CARRIER_CONFIG_CHANGED} to indicate the
     * subscription index that the broadcast is for, if a valid one is available.

variables.name: SERVICE_CLASS_NONE
variables.comment:
* Service class flag if no specific service class is specified.
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 27.007 Section 7.4 Facility lock +CLCK

variables.name: SERVICE_CLASS_VOICE
variables.comment:
* Service class flag for voice telephony.
     * Reference: 3GPP TS 27.007 Section 7.4 Facility lock +CLCK

variables.name: USSD_OVER_CS_PREFERRED
variables.comment:
* Only send USSD over IMS while CS is out of service, otherwise send USSD over CS.
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_USSD_METHOD_INT}

variables.name: USSD_OVER_IMS_PREFERRED
variables.comment:
* Send USSD over IMS or CS while IMS is out of service or silent redial over CS if needed.
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_USSD_METHOD_INT}

variables.name: USSD_OVER_CS_ONLY
variables.comment:
* Only send USSD over CS.
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_USSD_METHOD_INT}

variables.name: USSD_OVER_IMS_ONLY
variables.comment:
* Only send USSD over IMS and disallow silent redial over CS.
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_USSD_METHOD_INT}

variables.name: CARRIER_NR_AVAILABILITY_NSA
variables.comment:
* Indicates CARRIER_NR_AVAILABILITY_NSA determine that the carrier enable the non-standalone
     * (NSA) mode of 5G NR.

variables.name: CARRIER_NR_AVAILABILITY_SA
variables.comment:
* Indicates CARRIER_NR_AVAILABILITY_SA determine that the carrier enable the standalone (SA)
     * mode of 5G NR.

variables.name: ACTION_CARRIER_CONFIG_CHANGED
variables.comment:
* This intent is broadcast by the system when carrier config changes. An int is specified in
     * {@link #EXTRA_SLOT_INDEX} to indicate the slot index that this is for. An optional int extra
     * {@link #EXTRA_SUBSCRIPTION_INDEX} is included to indicate the subscription index if a valid
     * one is available for the slot index. An optional int extra
     * {@link TelephonyManager#EXTRA_CARRIER_ID} is included to indicate the carrier id for the
     * changed carrier configuration. An optional int extra
     * {@link TelephonyManager#EXTRA_SPECIFIC_CARRIER_ID} is included to indicate the precise
     * carrier id for the changed carrier configuration.
     * @see TelephonyManager#getSimCarrierId()
     * @see TelephonyManager#getSimSpecificCarrierId()

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_CONFIG_VERSION_STRING
variables.comment:
* Specifies a value that identifies the version of the carrier configuration that is
     * currently in use. This string is displayed on the UI.
     * The format of the string is not specified.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VOLTE_PROVISIONED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* This flag specifies whether VoLTE availability is based on provisioning. By default this is
     * false.
     * Used for UCE to determine if EAB provisioning checks should be based on provisioning.
     * @deprecated Use {@link Ims#KEY_CARRIER_RCS_PROVISIONING_REQUIRED_BOOL} instead.

variables.name: KEY_DISABLE_SUPPLEMENTARY_SERVICES_IN_AIRPLANE_MODE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating the Supplementary Services(SS) is disable when airplane mode on in the
     * Call Settings menu.
     * {@code true}: SS is disable when airplane mode on.
     * {@code false}: SS is enable when airplane mode on.
     * The default value for this key is {@code false}

variables.name: KEY_CALL_FORWARDING_VISIBILITY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating if the "Call forwarding" item is visible in the Call Settings menu.
     * true means visible. false means gone.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CALL_FORWARDING_WHEN_UNREACHABLE_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating if carrier supports call forwarding option "When unreachable".
     *
     * {@code true}: Call forwarding option "When unreachable" is supported.
     * {@code false}: Call forwarding option "When unreachable" is not supported. Option will be
     * removed in the UI.
     *
     * By default this value is true.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CALL_FORWARDING_WHEN_UNANSWERED_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating if carrier supports call forwarding option "When unanswered".
     *
     * {@code true}: Call forwarding option "When unanswered" is supported.
     * {@code false}: Call forwarding option "When unanswered" is not supported. Option will be
     * removed in the UI.
     *
     * By default this value is true.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CALL_FORWARDING_WHEN_BUSY_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating if carrier supports call forwarding option "When busy".
     *
     * {@code true}: Call forwarding option "When busy" is supported.
     * {@code false}: Call forwarding option "When busy" is not supported. Option will be
     * removed in the UI.
     *
     * By default this value is true.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_ADDITIONAL_SETTINGS_CALLER_ID_VISIBILITY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating if the "Caller ID" item is visible in the Additional Settings menu.
     * true means visible. false means gone.
     *
     * The default value is true.

variables.name: KEY_ADDITIONAL_SETTINGS_CALL_WAITING_VISIBILITY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating if the "Call Waiting" item is visible in the Additional Settings menu.
     * true means visible. false means gone.
     *
     * The default value is true.

variables.name: KEY_CALL_BARRING_VISIBILITY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Boolean indicating if the "Call barring" item is visible in the Call Settings menu.
     * If true, the "Call Barring" menu will be visible. If false, the menu will be gone.
     *
     * Disabled by default.

variables.name: KEY_CALL_BARRING_SUPPORTS_PASSWORD_CHANGE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether or not changing the call barring password via the "Call Barring"
     * settings menu is supported. If true, the option will be visible in the "Call
     * Barring" settings menu. If false, the option will not be visible.
     *
     * Enabled by default.

variables.name: KEY_CALL_BARRING_SUPPORTS_DEACTIVATE_ALL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether or not deactivating all call barring features via the "Call Barring"
     * settings menu is supported. If true, the option will be visible in the "Call
     * Barring" settings menu. If false, the option will not be visible.
     *
     * Enabled by default.

variables.name: KEY_CALL_BARRING_DEFAULT_SERVICE_CLASS_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the service class for call barring service. Default value is * {@link #SERVICE_CLASS_VOICE}. * The value set as below: *
    *
  • 0: {@link #SERVICE_CLASS_NONE}
    • *
  • 1: {@link #SERVICE_CLASS_VOICE}
    • *

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_SS_OVER_CDMA_BOOL
variables.comment:
* This carrier supports dialing USSD codes to enable/disable supplementary services such as * call forwarding and call waiting over CDMA. *

* The supplementary service menu will still need to be set as visible, see * {@link #KEY_CALL_FORWARDING_VISIBILITY_BOOL} and * {@link #KEY_ADDITIONAL_SETTINGS_CALL_WAITING_VISIBILITY_BOOL}. *

* If this is set as false and the supplementary service menu is visible, the associated setting * will be enabled and disabled based on the availability of supplementary services over UT. See * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_SUPPORTS_SS_OVER_UT_BOOL}. * @hide

variables.name: KEY_IGNORE_SIM_NETWORK_LOCKED_EVENTS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether the Phone app should ignore EVENT_SIM_NETWORK_LOCKED
     * events from the Sim.
     * If true, this will prevent the IccNetworkDepersonalizationPanel from being shown, and
     * effectively disable the "Sim network lock" feature.

variables.name: KEY_MDN_IS_ADDITIONAL_VOICEMAIL_NUMBER_BOOL
variables.comment:
* When checking if a given number is the voicemail number, if this flag is true
     * then in addition to comparing the given number to the voicemail number, we also compare it
     * to the mdn. If this flag is false, the given number is only compared to the voicemail number.
     * By default this value is false.

variables.name: KEY_SIM_NETWORK_UNLOCK_ALLOW_DISMISS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether the Phone app should provide a "Dismiss" button on the SIM network
     * unlock screen. The default value is true. If set to false, there will be *no way* to dismiss
     * the SIM network unlock screen if you don't enter the correct unlock code. (One important
     * consequence: there will be no way to make an Emergency Call if your SIM is network-locked and
     * you don't know the PIN.)

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_EMERGENCY_SMS_OVER_IMS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether or not sending emergency SMS messages over IMS
     * is supported when in LTE/limited LTE (Emergency only) service mode..

variables.name: KEY_WORLD_PHONE_BOOL
variables.comment: Flag indicating if the phone is a world phone

variables.name: KEY_REQUIRE_ENTITLEMENT_CHECKS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag to require or skip entitlement checks.
     * If true, entitlement checks will be executed if device has been configured for it,
     * If false, entitlement checks will be skipped.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_SUPPORTS_TETHERING_BOOL
variables.comment: * Flag indicating if the carrier supports tethering of mobile data.

variables.name: KEY_RESTART_RADIO_ON_PDP_FAIL_REGULAR_DEACTIVATION_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether radio is to be restarted on error PDP_FAIL_REGULAR_DEACTIVATION
     * This is false by default.
     *
     * @deprecated Use {@link #KEY_RADIO_RESTART_FAILURE_CAUSES_INT_ARRAY} instead

variables.name: KEY_RADIO_RESTART_FAILURE_CAUSES_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A list of failure cause codes that will trigger a modem restart when telephony receiving
     * one of those during data setup. The cause codes are defined in 3GPP TS 24.008 Annex I and
     * TS 24.301 Annex B.

variables.name: KEY_ENABLE_DIALER_KEY_VIBRATION_BOOL
variables.comment:
* If true, enable vibration (haptic feedback) for key presses in the EmergencyDialer activity.
     * The pattern is set on a per-platform basis using config_virtualKeyVibePattern. To be
     * consistent with the regular Dialer, this value should agree with the corresponding values
     * from config.xml under apps/Contacts.

variables.name: KEY_DTMF_TYPE_ENABLED_BOOL
variables.comment: Flag indicating if dtmf tone type is enabled

variables.name: KEY_AUTO_RETRY_ENABLED_BOOL
variables.comment: Flag indicating if auto retry is enabled

variables.name: KEY_ALLOW_LOCAL_DTMF_TONES_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determine whether we want to play local DTMF tones in a call, or just let the radio/BP handle
     * playing of the tones.

variables.name: KEY_PLAY_CALL_RECORDING_TONE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines if the carrier requires that a tone be played to the remote party when an app is * recording audio during a call (e.g. using a call recording app). *

* Note: This requires the Telephony config_supports_telephony_audio_device overlay to be true * in order to work. * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SMS_REQUIRES_DESTINATION_NUMBER_CONVERSION_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines if the carrier requires converting the destination number before sending out an
     * SMS. Certain networks and numbering plans require different formats.

variables.name: KEY_SHOW_ONSCREEN_DIAL_BUTTON_BOOL
variables.comment:
* If true, show an onscreen "Dial" button in the dialer. In practice this is used on all
     * platforms, even the ones with hard SEND/END keys, but for maximum flexibility it's controlled
     * by a flag here (which can be overridden on a per-product basis.)

variables.name: KEY_HAS_IN_CALL_NOISE_SUPPRESSION_BOOL
variables.comment: Determines if device implements a noise suppression device for in call audio.

variables.name: KEY_ALLOW_EMERGENCY_NUMBERS_IN_CALL_LOG_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines if the current device should allow emergency numbers to be logged in the Call Log.
     * (Some carriers require that emergency calls *not* be logged, presumably to avoid the risk of
     * accidental redialing from the call log UI. This is a good idea, so the default here is
     * false.)

variables.name: KEY_UNLOGGABLE_NUMBERS_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment: * A string array containing numbers that shouldn't be included in the call log.

variables.name: KEY_VOICE_PRIVACY_DISABLE_UI_BOOL
variables.comment: If true, removes the Voice Privacy option from Call Settings

variables.name: KEY_HIDE_CARRIER_NETWORK_SETTINGS_BOOL
variables.comment: Control whether users can reach the carrier portions of Cellular Network Settings.

variables.name: KEY_ONLY_AUTO_SELECT_IN_HOME_NETWORK_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Only allow auto selection in Advanced Network Settings when in home network.
     * Manual selection is allowed when in roaming network.

variables.name: KEY_SHOW_SINGLE_OPERATOR_ROW_IN_CHOOSE_NETWORK_SETTING_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether to show single operator row in the choose network setting.
     *
     * The device configuration value {@code config_enableNewAutoSelectNetworkUI} ultimately
     * controls whether this carrier configuration option is used.
     * Where {@code config_enableNewAutoSelectNetworkUI} is false, the value of this
     * carrier configuration is ignored.
     *
     * If {@code true}, default value, merge the duplicate networks which with the same plmn, keep
     * the one that with the higher signal strength level.
     * If {@code false}, show all operators without merging.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SHOW_SPN_FOR_HOME_IN_CHOOSE_NETWORK_SETTING_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether to display SPN as network name for home network in choose
     * network setting.
     *
     * If {@code true}, display SPN as network name in choose network setting.
     * If {@code false}, display PLMN in choose network setting.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SIMPLIFIED_NETWORK_SETTINGS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Control whether users receive a simplified network settings UI and improved network
     * selection.
     *
     * @deprecated Never implemented. Has no behavior impact when override. DO NOT USE.

variables.name: KEY_HIDE_SIM_LOCK_SETTINGS_BOOL
variables.comment: Control whether users can reach the SIM lock settings.

variables.name: KEY_APN_EXPAND_BOOL
variables.comment: Control whether users can edit APNs in Settings.

variables.name: KEY_OPERATOR_SELECTION_EXPAND_BOOL
variables.comment: Control whether users can choose a network operator.

variables.name: KEY_PREFER_2G_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Used in the Preferred Network Types menu to determine if the 2G option is displayed.
     * Value defaults to false as of Android T to discourage the use of insecure 2G protocols.

variables.name: KEY_PREFER_3G_VISIBILITY_BOOL
variables.comment: * Used in the Preferred Network Types menu to determine if the 3G option is displayed.

variables.name: KEY_4G_ONLY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Used in Cellular Network Settings for preferred network type to show 4G only mode.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SHOW_CDMA_CHOICES_BOOL
variables.comment: Show cdma network mode choices 1x, 3G, global etc.

variables.name: KEY_USE_HFA_FOR_PROVISIONING_BOOL
variables.comment: CDMA activation goes through HFA

variables.name: KEY_USE_OTASP_FOR_PROVISIONING_BOOL
variables.comment: (NONE, HFA, OTASP).

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_SETTINGS_ENABLE_BOOL
variables.comment: Display carrier settings menu if true

variables.name: KEY_ADDITIONAL_CALL_SETTING_BOOL
variables.comment: Does not display additional call setting for IMS phone based on GSM Phone

variables.name: KEY_SHOW_APN_SETTING_CDMA_BOOL
variables.comment: Show APN Settings for some CDMA carriers

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_SWAP_AFTER_MERGE_BOOL
variables.comment: After a CDMA conference call is merged, the swap button should be displayed.

variables.name: KEY_EDITABLE_VOICEMAIL_NUMBER_SETTING_BOOL
variables.comment: * Determine whether user can edit voicemail number in Settings.

variables.name: KEY_EDITABLE_VOICEMAIL_NUMBER_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Since the default voicemail number is empty, if a SIM card does not have a voicemail number
     * available the user cannot use voicemail. This flag allows the user to edit the voicemail
     * number in such cases, and is false by default.

variables.name: KEY_HIDE_VOICEMAIL_NUMBER_SETTING_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determine whether the voicemail number in Settings is hidden.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_VOICEMAIL_NOTIFICATION_PERSISTENT_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determine whether the voicemail notification is persistent in the notification bar. If true,
     * the voicemail notifications cannot be dismissed from the notification bar.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_PAUSE_IMS_VIDEO_CALLS_BOOL
variables.comment: For IMS video over LTE calls, determines whether video pause signalling is supported.

variables.name: KEY_DISABLE_CDMA_ACTIVATION_CODE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Disables dialing "*228" (OTASP provisioning) on CDMA carriers where it is not supported or is
     * potentially harmful by locking the SIM to 3G.

variables.name: KEY_ONLY_SINGLE_DC_ALLOWED_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* List of network type constants which support only a single data connection at a time.
     * Some carriers do not support multiple PDP on UMTS.
     * @see TelephonyManager NETWORK_TYPE_*
     * @see #KEY_ONLY_SINGLE_DC_ALLOWED_INT_ARRAY

variables.name: KEY_CAPABILITIES_EXEMPT_FROM_SINGLE_DC_CHECK_INT_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Only apply if {@link #KEY_ONLY_SINGLE_DC_ALLOWED_INT_ARRAY} specifies the network types that
     * support a single data connection at a time. This key defines a list of network capabilities
     * which, if requested, will exempt the request from single data connection checks.
     * @see NetworkCapabilities NET_CAPABILITY_*

variables.name: KEY_GSM_ROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Override the platform's notion of a network operator being considered roaming.
     * Value is string array of MCCMNCs to be considered roaming for 3GPP RATs.

variables.name: KEY_GSM_NONROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Override the platform's notion of a network operator being considered not roaming.
     * Value is string array of MCCMNCs to be considered not roaming for 3GPP RATs.

variables.name: KEY_CONFIG_IMS_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* The package name containing the ImsService that will be bound to the telephony framework to
     * support both IMS MMTEL and RCS feature functionality instead of the device default
     * ImsService for this subscription.
     * @deprecated Use {@link #KEY_CONFIG_IMS_MMTEL_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING} and
     * {@link #KEY_CONFIG_IMS_RCS_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING} instead to configure these values
     * separately. If any of those values are not empty, they will override this value.

variables.name: KEY_CONFIG_IMS_MMTEL_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* The package name containing the ImsService that will be bound to the telephony framework to
     * support IMS MMTEL feature functionality instead of the device default ImsService for this
     * subscription.

variables.name: KEY_CONFIG_IMS_RCS_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* The package name containing the ImsService that will be bound to the telephony framework to
     * support IMS RCS feature functionality instead of the device default ImsService for this
     * subscription.

variables.name: KEY_CONFIG_PLANS_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* Override the package that will manage {@link SubscriptionPlan}
     * information instead of the {@link CarrierService} that defines this
     * value.
     *
     * @see SubscriptionManager#getSubscriptionPlans(int)
     * @see SubscriptionManager#setSubscriptionPlans(int, java.util.List)

variables.name: KEY_CDMA_ROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Override the platform's notion of a network operator being considered roaming.
     * Value is string array of SIDs to be considered roaming for 3GPP2 RATs.

variables.name: KEY_CDMA_NONROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Override the platform's notion of a network operator being considered non roaming.
     * Value is string array of SIDs to be considered not roaming for 3GPP2 RATs.

variables.name: KEY_FORCE_HOME_NETWORK_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Override the platform's notion of a network operator being considered non roaming.
     * If true all networks are considered as home network a.k.a. non-roaming. When false,
     * the 2 pairs of CMDA and GSM roaming/non-roaming arrays are consulted.
     *
     * @see #KEY_GSM_ROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY
     * @see #KEY_GSM_NONROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY
     * @see #KEY_CDMA_ROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY
     * @see #KEY_CDMA_NONROAMING_NETWORKS_STRING_ARRAY

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VOLTE_AVAILABLE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether VoLTE should be available for carrier, independent of carrier
     * provisioning. If false: hard disabled. If true: then depends on carrier provisioning,
     * availability, etc.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VT_AVAILABLE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether video telephony is available for carrier. If false: hard disabled.
     * If true: then depends on carrier provisioning, availability, etc.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_USSD_METHOD_INT
variables.comment:
* Specify the method of selection for UE sending USSD requests. The default value is * {@link #USSD_OVER_CS_PREFERRED}. *

Available options: *

    *
  • 0: {@link #USSD_OVER_CS_PREFERRED}
    • *
  • 1: {@link #USSD_OVER_IMS_PREFERRED}
    • *
  • 2: {@link #USSD_OVER_CS_ONLY}
    • *
  • 3: {@link #USSD_OVER_IMS_ONLY}
    • *

variables.name: KEY_VOLTE_5G_LIMITED_ALERT_DIALOG_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether to show an alert dialog for 5G disable when the user disables VoLTE.
     * By default this value is {@code false}.
     *
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_NOTIFY_HANDOVER_VIDEO_FROM_WIFI_TO_LTE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether the carrier wants to notify the user when a VT call has been handed * over from WIFI to LTE. *

* The handover notification is sent as a * {@link TelephonyManager#EVENT_HANDOVER_VIDEO_FROM_WIFI_TO_LTE} * {@link android.telecom.Connection} event, which an {@link android.telecom.InCallService} * should use to trigger the display of a user-facing message. *

* The Connection event is sent to the InCallService only once, the first time it occurs. * @hide

variables.name: KEY_ALLOW_MERGING_RTT_CALLS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether the carrier supports merging a RTT call with a voice call,
     * downgrading the call in the process.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_NOTIFY_HANDOVER_VIDEO_FROM_LTE_TO_WIFI_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether the carrier wants to notify the user when a VT call has been handed * over from LTE to WIFI. *

* The handover notification is sent as a * {@link TelephonyManager#EVENT_HANDOVER_VIDEO_FROM_LTE_TO_WIFI} * {@link android.telecom.Connection} event, which an {@link android.telecom.InCallService} * should use to trigger the display of a user-facing message. * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_DOWNGRADE_VT_TO_AUDIO_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether the carrier supports downgrading a video call (tx, rx or tx/rx)
     * directly to an audio call.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_DEFAULT_VM_NUMBER_STRING
variables.comment:
* Where there is no preloaded voicemail number on a SIM card, specifies the carrier's default
     * voicemail number.
     * When empty string, no default voicemail number is specified.

variables.name: KEY_DEFAULT_VM_NUMBER_ROAMING_STRING
variables.comment:
* Where there is no preloaded voicemail number on a SIM card, specifies the carrier's default
     * voicemail number for roaming network.
     * When empty string, no default voicemail number is specified for roaming network.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_DEFAULT_VM_NUMBER_ROAMING_AND_IMS_UNREGISTERED_STRING
variables.comment:
* Where there is no preloaded voicemail number on a SIM card, specifies the carrier's default
     * voicemail number while the device is both roaming and not registered for IMS.
     * When empty string, no default voicemail number is specified for roaming network and
     * unregistered state in IMS.

variables.name: KEY_CONFIG_TELEPHONY_USE_OWN_NUMBER_FOR_VOICEMAIL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag that specifies to use the user's own phone number as the voicemail number when there is * no pre-loaded voicemail number on the SIM card. *

* {@link #KEY_DEFAULT_VM_NUMBER_STRING} takes precedence over this flag. *

* If false, the system default (*86) will be used instead.

variables.name: KEY_IGNORE_DATA_ENABLED_CHANGED_FOR_VIDEO_CALLS
variables.comment:
* When {@code true}, changes to the mobile data enabled switch will not cause the VT
     * registration state to change. That is, turning on or off mobile data will not cause VT to be
     * enabled or disabled.
     * When {@code false}, disabling mobile data will cause VT to be de-registered.

variables.name: KEY_VILTE_DATA_IS_METERED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether data used for a video call over LTE is metered or not. *

* When {@code true}, if the device hits the data limit or data is disabled during a ViLTE call, * the call will be downgraded to audio-only (or paused if * {@link #KEY_SUPPORT_PAUSE_IMS_VIDEO_CALLS_BOOL} is {@code true}). * * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_WFC_IMS_AVAILABLE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether WFC over IMS should be available for carrier: independent of
     * carrier provisioning. If false: hard disabled. If true: then depends on carrier
     * provisioning, availability etc.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_CROSS_SIM_IMS_AVAILABLE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether Cross SIM over IMS should be available for carrier.
     * When {@code false} the carrier does not support cross SIM calling.
     * When {@code true} the carrier does support cross sim calling, where available

variables.name: KEY_ENABLE_CROSS_SIM_CALLING_ON_OPPORTUNISTIC_DATA_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether cross sim calling on opportunistic data is supported for carrier.
     * When {@code false} the carrier does not support cross sim calling on opportunistic data.
     * When {@code true} the carrier does support cross sim calling on opportunistic data.

variables.name: KEY_DIAL_STRING_REPLACE_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Specifies a map from dialstrings to replacements for roaming network service numbers which * cannot be replaced on the carrier side. *

* Individual entries have the format: * [dialstring to replace]:[replacement]

variables.name: KEY_INTERNATIONAL_ROAMING_DIAL_STRING_REPLACE_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* Specifies a map from dialstrings to replacements for international roaming network service * numbers which cannot be replaced on the carrier side. *

* Individual entries have the format: * [dialstring to replace]:[replacement] * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_WFC_SUPPORTS_WIFI_ONLY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether WFC over IMS supports the "wifi only" option. If false, the wifi * calling settings will not include an option for "wifi only". If true, the wifi calling * settings will include an option for "wifi only" *

* By default, it is assumed that WFC supports "wifi only".

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DEFAULT_WFC_IMS_MODE_INT
variables.comment:
* Default mode for WFC over IMS on home network: *
    *
  • 0: Wi-Fi only *
  • 1: prefer mobile network *
  • 2: prefer Wi-Fi *

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DEFAULT_WFC_IMS_ROAMING_MODE_INT
variables.comment:
* Default mode for WFC over IMS on roaming network.
     * See {@link #KEY_CARRIER_DEFAULT_WFC_IMS_MODE_INT} for meaning of values.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DEFAULT_WFC_IMS_ENABLED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Default WFC_IMS_enabled: true VoWiFi by default is on
     *                          false VoWiFi by default is off

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DEFAULT_WFC_IMS_ROAMING_ENABLED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Default WFC_IMS_roaming_enabled: true VoWiFi roaming by default is on
     *                                  false VoWiFi roaming by default is off
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_PROMOTE_WFC_ON_CALL_FAIL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether failed calls due to no service should prompt the user to enable
     * WIFI calling. When {@code true}, if the user attempts to establish a call when there is no
     * service available, they are connected to WIFI, and WIFI calling is disabled, a different
     * call failure message will be used to encourage the user to enable WIFI calling.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_RCS_PROVISIONING_REQUIRED_BOOL
variables.comment: * Flag specifying whether provisioning is required for RCS.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VOLTE_PROVISIONING_REQUIRED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether provisioning is required for VoLTE, Video Telephony, and WiFi
     * Calling.

     * Combines VoLTE, VT, VoWiFI calling provisioning into one parameter.
     * @deprecated Use {@link Ims#KEY_MMTEL_REQUIRES_PROVISIONING_BUNDLE} instead for
     * finer-grained control.
     * changing carrier_volte_provisioning_required_bool requires changes to
     * mmtel_requires_provisioning_bundle and vice versa
     * {@link Ims#KEY_MMTEL_REQUIRES_PROVISIONING_BUNDLE}

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_UT_PROVISIONING_REQUIRED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether or not the IMS MmTel UT capability requires carrier provisioning
     * before it can be set as enabled.
     *
     * If true, the UT capability will be set to false for the newly loaded subscription
     * and will require the carrier provisioning app to set the persistent provisioning result.
     * If false, the platform will not wait for provisioning status updates for the UT capability
     * and enable the UT over IMS capability for the subscription when the subscription is loaded.
     *
     * The default value for this key is {@code false}.
     *
     * @deprecated Use {@link Ims#KEY_MMTEL_REQUIRES_PROVISIONING_BUNDLE} instead for
     * determining if UT requires provisioning.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_SUPPORTS_SS_OVER_UT_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag indicating whether or not the carrier supports Supplementary Services over the UT
     * interface for this subscription.
     *
     * If true, the device will use Supplementary Services over UT when provisioned (see
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_UT_PROVISIONING_REQUIRED_BOOL}). If false, this device will fallback to
     * circuit switch for supplementary services and will disable this capability for IMS entirely.
     *
     * The default value for this key is {@code false}.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VOLTE_OVERRIDE_WFC_PROVISIONING_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying if WFC provisioning depends on VoLTE provisioning.
     *
     * {@code false}: default value; honor actual WFC provisioning state.
     * {@code true}: when VoLTE is not provisioned, treat WFC as not provisioned; when VoLTE is
     *               provisioned, honor actual WFC provisioning state.
     *
     * As of now, Verizon is the only carrier enforcing this dependency in their
     * WFC awareness and activation requirements.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DATA_SERVICE_WWAN_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* Override the device's configuration for the cellular data service to use for this SIM card.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DATA_SERVICE_WLAN_PACKAGE_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* Override the device's configuration for the IWLAN data service to use for this SIM card.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DATA_SERVICE_WWAN_CLASS_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* Override the device's configuration for the cellular data service class to use
     * for this SIM card.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DATA_SERVICE_WLAN_CLASS_OVERRIDE_STRING
variables.comment:
* Override the device's configuration for the IWLAN data service class to use
     * for this SIM card.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VOLTE_TTY_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment: Flag specifying whether VoLTE TTY is supported.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VOWIFI_TTY_SUPPORTED_BOOL
variables.comment:
Flag specifying whether VoWIFI TTY is supported.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_ALLOW_TURNOFF_IMS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether IMS service can be turned off. If false then the service will not be
     * turned-off completely, but individual features can be disabled.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_IMS_GBA_REQUIRED_BOOL
variables.comment: * Flag specifying whether Generic Bootstrapping Architecture capable SIM is required for IMS.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_AVAILABLE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether IMS instant lettering is available for the carrier. {@code True} if
     * instant lettering is available for the carrier, {@code false} otherwise.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_USE_IMS_FIRST_FOR_EMERGENCY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether IMS should be the first phone attempted for E911 even if the
     * phone is not in service.

variables.name: KEY_PREFER_IN_SERVICE_SIM_FOR_NORMAL_ROUTED_EMERGENCY_CALLS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* When {@code true}, this carrier will preferentially dial normal routed emergency calls over
     * an in-service SIM if one is available.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_USE_ONLY_DIALED_SIM_ECC_LIST_BOOL
variables.comment:
* When {@code true}, the determination of whether to place a call as an emergency call will be
     * based on the known {@link android.telephony.emergency.EmergencyNumber}s for the SIM on which
     * the call is being placed. In a dual SIM scenario, if Sim A has the emergency numbers
     * 123, 456 and Sim B has the emergency numbers 789, and the user places a call on SIM A to 789,
     * it will not be treated as an emergency call in this case.
     * When {@code false}, the determination is based on the emergency numbers from all device SIMs,
     * regardless of which SIM the call is being placed on. If Sim A has the emergency numbers
     * 123, 456 and Sim B has the emergency numbers 789, and the user places a call on SIM A to 789,
     * the call will be dialed as an emergency number, but with an unspecified routing.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_INVALID_CHARS_STRING
variables.comment:
* When IMS instant lettering is available for a carrier (see
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_AVAILABLE_BOOL}), determines the list of characters
     * which may not be contained in messages. Should be specified as a regular expression suitable
     * for use with {@link String#matches(String)}.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_ESCAPED_CHARS_STRING
variables.comment:
* When IMS instant lettering is available for a carrier (see
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_AVAILABLE_BOOL}), determines a list of characters which
     * must be escaped with a backslash '\' character. Should be specified as a string containing
     * the characters to be escaped. For example to escape quote and backslash the string would be
     * a quote and a backslash.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_ENCODING_STRING
variables.comment:
* When IMS instant lettering is available for a carrier (see
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_AVAILABLE_BOOL}), determines the character encoding
     * which will be used when determining the length of messages. Used in the InCall UI to limit
     * the number of characters the user may type. If empty-string, the instant lettering
     * message size limit will be enforced on a 1:1 basis. That is, each character will count
     * towards the messages size limit as a single byte. If a character encoding is specified, the
     * message size limit will be based on the number of bytes in the message per the specified
     * encoding.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_LENGTH_LIMIT_INT
variables.comment:
* When IMS instant lettering is available for a carrier (see
     * {@link #KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_AVAILABLE_BOOL}), the length limit for messages. Used
     * in the InCall UI to ensure the user cannot enter more characters than allowed by the carrier.
     * See also {@link #KEY_CARRIER_INSTANT_LETTERING_ENCODING_STRING} for more information on how
     * the length of the message is calculated.

variables.name: KEY_VOLTE_REPLACEMENT_RAT_INT
variables.comment:
* If Voice Radio Technology is RIL_RADIO_TECHNOLOGY_LTE:14 or RIL_RADIO_TECHNOLOGY_UNKNOWN:0
     * this is the value that should be used instead. A configuration value of
     * RIL_RADIO_TECHNOLOGY_UNKNOWN:0 means there is no replacement value and that the default
     * assumption for phone type (GSM) should be used.

variables.name: KEY_DEFAULT_SIM_CALL_MANAGER_STRING
variables.comment:
* The default sim call manager to use when the default dialer doesn't implement one. A sim call
     * manager can control and route outgoing and incoming phone calls, even if they're placed
     * using another connection service (PSTN, for example).

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_FORCE_DISABLE_ETWS_CMAS_TEST_BOOL
variables.comment:
* The default flag specifying whether ETWS/CMAS test setting is forcibly disabled in
     * Settings->More->Emergency broadcasts menu even though developer options is turned on.
     * @deprecated Use {@code com.android.cellbroadcastreceiver.CellBroadcastReceiver} resource
     * {@code show_test_settings} to control whether to show test alert settings or not.

variables.name: KEY_ALWAYS_SHOW_EMERGENCY_ALERT_ONOFF_BOOL
variables.comment:
* The default flag specifying whether "Allow alerts" option will be always shown in
     * emergency alerts settings regardless developer options is turned on or not.
     *
     * @deprecated The allow alerts option is always shown now. No longer need a config for that.

variables.name: KEY_DEFAULT_MTU_INT
variables.comment:
* Default mobile network MTU value, in bytes.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DATA_CALL_APN_RETRY_AFTER_DISCONNECT_LONG
variables.comment:
* Delay in milliseconds for retrying APN after disconnect
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_DATA_CALL_PERMANENT_FAILURE_STRINGS
variables.comment:
* Data call setup permanent failure causes by the carrier.
     *
     * @deprecated This API key was added in mistake and is not used anymore by the telephony data
     * frameworks.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_METERED_APN_TYPES_STRINGS
variables.comment:
* A string array indicating the default APN types that are metered by the carrier.
     *
     * The string in the array is the name of the APN type. For example, "default" for
     * {@link ApnSetting#TYPE_DEFAULT}, "mms" for {@link ApnSetting#TYPE_MMS}, etc.
     *
     * The default value is {@code {"default", "mms", "dun", "supl"}}.
     *
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_DEFAULT
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_MMS
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_SUPL
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_DUN
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_HIPRI
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_FOTA
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_IMS
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_CBS
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_IA
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_EMERGENCY
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_MCX
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_XCAP
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_BIP
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_VSIM
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_ENTERPRISE

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_METERED_ROAMING_APN_TYPES_STRINGS
variables.comment:
* A string array indicating the default APN types that are roaming-metered by the carrier.
     *
     * The string in the array is the name of the APN type. For example, "default" for
     * {@link ApnSetting#TYPE_DEFAULT}, "mms" for {@link ApnSetting#TYPE_MMS}, etc.
     *
     * The default value is {@code {"default", "mms", "dun", "supl"}}.
     *
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_DEFAULT
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_MMS
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_SUPL
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_DUN
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_HIPRI
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_FOTA
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_IMS
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_CBS
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_IA
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_EMERGENCY
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_MCX
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_XCAP
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_BIP
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_VSIM
     * @see ApnSetting#TYPE_ENTERPRISE

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_ERI_FILE_NAME_STRING
variables.comment:
* CDMA carrier ERI (Enhanced Roaming Indicator) file name
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_VVM_DESTINATION_NUMBER_STRING
variables.comment: * The carrier number mobile outgoing (MO) sms messages are sent to.

variables.name: KEY_VVM_PORT_NUMBER_INT
variables.comment: * The port through which the mobile outgoing (MO) sms messages are sent through.

variables.name: KEY_VVM_TYPE_STRING
variables.comment:
* The type of visual voicemail protocol the carrier adheres to. See {@link TelephonyManager}
     * for possible values. For example {@link TelephonyManager#VVM_TYPE_OMTP}.

variables.name: KEY_VVM_CELLULAR_DATA_REQUIRED_BOOL
variables.comment: * Whether cellular data is required to access visual voicemail.

variables.name: KEY_VVM_CLIENT_PREFIX_STRING
variables.comment: * The default OMTP visual voicemail client prefix to use. Defaulted to "//VVM"

variables.name: KEY_VVM_SSL_ENABLED_BOOL
variables.comment: * Whether to use SSL to connect to the visual voicemail IMAP server. Defaulted to false.

variables.name: KEY_VVM_DISABLED_CAPABILITIES_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A set of capabilities that should not be used even if it is reported by the visual voicemail
     * IMAP CAPABILITY command.

variables.name: KEY_VVM_LEGACY_MODE_ENABLED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Whether legacy mode should be used when the visual voicemail client is disabled. * *

Legacy mode is a mode that on the carrier side visual voicemail is still activated, but on * the client side all network operations are disabled. SMSs are still monitored so a new * message SYNC SMS will be translated to show a message waiting indicator, like traditional * voicemails. * *

This is for carriers that does not support VVM deactivation so voicemail can continue to * function without the data cost.

variables.name: KEY_VVM_PREFETCH_BOOL
variables.comment: * Whether to prefetch audio data on new voicemail arrival, defaulted to true.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VVM_PACKAGE_NAME_STRING
variables.comment:
* The package name of the carrier's visual voicemail app to ensure that dialer visual voicemail
     * and carrier visual voicemail are not active at the same time.
     *
     * @deprecated use {@link #KEY_CARRIER_VVM_PACKAGE_NAME_STRING_ARRAY}.

variables.name: KEY_CARRIER_VVM_PACKAGE_NAME_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* A list of the carrier's visual voicemail app package names to ensure that dialer visual
     * voicemail and carrier visual voicemail are not active at the same time.

variables.name: KEY_SHOW_ICCID_IN_SIM_STATUS_BOOL
variables.comment: * Flag specifying whether ICCID is showed in SIM Status screen, default to false.

variables.name: KEY_SHOW_SIGNAL_STRENGTH_IN_SIM_STATUS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether the {@link android.telephony.SignalStrength} is shown in the SIM
     * Status screen. The default value is true.

variables.name: KEY_INFLATE_SIGNAL_STRENGTH_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying if we should interpret all signal strength as one bar higher
     * This is a replacement for the former resource config_inflateSignalStrength
     * The default value is false.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_CI_ACTION_ON_SYS_UPDATE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Flag specifying whether an additional (client initiated) intent needs to be sent on System
     * update

variables.name: KEY_CI_ACTION_ON_SYS_UPDATE_INTENT_STRING
variables.comment: * Intent to be sent for the additional action on System update

variables.name: KEY_CI_ACTION_ON_SYS_UPDATE_EXTRA_STRING
variables.comment: * Extra to be included in the intent sent for additional action on System update

variables.name: KEY_CI_ACTION_ON_SYS_UPDATE_EXTRA_VAL_STRING
variables.comment: * Value of extra included in intent sent for additional action on System update

variables.name: KEY_GSM_DTMF_TONE_DELAY_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the amount of gap to be added in millis between postdial DTMF tones. When a
     * non-zero value is specified, the UE shall wait for the specified amount of time before it
     * sends out successive DTMF tones on the network.

variables.name: KEY_IMS_DTMF_TONE_DELAY_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the amount of gap to be added in millis between DTMF tones. When a non-zero value
     * is specified, the UE shall wait for the specified amount of time before it sends out
     * successive DTMF tones on the network.

variables.name: KEY_CDMA_DTMF_TONE_DELAY_INT
variables.comment:
* Specifies the amount of gap to be added in millis between postdial DTMF tones. When a
     * non-zero value is specified, the UE shall wait for the specified amount of time before it
     * sends out successive DTMF tones on the network.

variables.name: KEY_CALL_FORWARDING_MAP_NON_NUMBER_TO_VOICEMAIL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Some carriers will send call forwarding responses for voicemail in a format that is not 3gpp
     * compliant, which causes issues during parsing. This causes the
     * {@link com.android.internal.telephony.CallForwardInfo#number} to contain non-numerical
     * characters instead of a number.
     *
     * If true, we will detect the non-numerical characters and replace them with "Voicemail".
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_IGNORE_RTT_MODE_SETTING_BOOL
variables.comment:
* When {@code true}, the phone will always tell the IMS stack to keep RTT enabled and
     * determine on a per-call basis (based on extras from the dialer app) whether a call should be
     * an RTT call or not.
     *
     * When {@code false}, the old behavior is used, where the toggle in accessibility settings is
     * used to set the IMS stack's RTT enabled state.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_ADHOC_CONFERENCE_CALLS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether adhoc conference calls are supported by a carrier. When {@code true},
     * adhoc conference calling is supported, {@code false otherwise}.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_ADD_CONFERENCE_PARTICIPANTS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether conference participants can be added to existing call to form an adhoc
     * conference call (in contrast to merging calls to form a conference). When {@code true},
     * adding conference participants to existing call is supported, {@code false otherwise}.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_CONFERENCE_CALL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether conference calls are supported by a carrier. When {@code true},
     * conference calling is supported, {@code false otherwise}.

variables.name: KEY_IS_IMS_CONFERENCE_SIZE_ENFORCED_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether a maximum size limit for IMS conference calls is enforced on the device. * When {@code true}, IMS conference calls will be limited to at most * {@link #KEY_IMS_CONFERENCE_SIZE_LIMIT_INT} participants. When {@code false}, no attempt is * made to limit the number of participants in a conference (the carrier will raise an error * when an attempt is made to merge too many participants into a conference). *

* Note: The maximum size of a conference can ONLY be supported where * {@link #KEY_SUPPORT_IMS_CONFERENCE_EVENT_PACKAGE_BOOL} is {@code true} since the platform * needs conference event package data to accurately know the number of participants in the * conference.

variables.name: KEY_IMS_CONFERENCE_SIZE_LIMIT_INT
variables.comment:
* Determines the maximum number of participants the carrier supports for a conference call.
     * This number is exclusive of the current device. A conference between 3 devices, for example,
     * would have a size limit of 2 participants.
     * Enforced when {@link #KEY_IS_IMS_CONFERENCE_SIZE_ENFORCED_BOOL} is {@code true}.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_MANAGE_IMS_CONFERENCE_CALL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether manage IMS conference calls is supported by a carrier. When {@code true},
     * manage IMS conference call is supported, {@code false otherwise}.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_IMS_CONFERENCE_EVENT_PACKAGE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether the IMS conference merge process supports and returns its participants
     * data. When {@code true}, on merge complete, conference call would have a list of its
     * participants returned in XML format, {@code false otherwise}.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_IMS_CONFERENCE_EVENT_PACKAGE_ON_PEER_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether processing of conference event package data received on a device other * than the conference host is supported. *

* When a device A merges calls B and C into a conference it is considered the conference host * and B and C are considered the conference peers. *

* When {@code true}, the conference peer will display the conference state if it receives * conference event package data from the network. When {@code false}, the conference peer will * ignore conference event package data received from the network. * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTS_DEVICE_TO_DEVICE_COMMUNICATION_USING_RTP_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Indicates whether the carrier supports the use of RFC8285 compliant RTP header extensions for * the purpose of device to device communication while in a call. *

* See also {@link #KEY_SUPPORTS_SDP_NEGOTIATION_OF_D2D_RTP_HEADER_EXTENSIONS_BOOL}.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTS_SDP_NEGOTIATION_OF_D2D_RTP_HEADER_EXTENSIONS_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Indicates whether the carrier supports the negotiations of RFC8285 compliant RTP header * extensions supported on a call during the Session Description Protocol (SDP). This option * is only used when {@link #KEY_SUPPORTS_DEVICE_TO_DEVICE_COMMUNICATION_USING_RTP_BOOL} is * {@code true}. *

* When {@code true}, the RTP header extensions the platform uses for device to device * communication will be offered to the remote end during the SDP negotiation process. * When {@code false}, the RTP header extensions will not be negotiated during the SDP * negotiation process and the platform will send RTP header extensions without prior * negotiation if {@link #KEY_SUPPORTS_DEVICE_TO_DEVICE_COMMUNICATION_USING_RTP_BOOL} is * {@code true}.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORTS_DEVICE_TO_DEVICE_COMMUNICATION_USING_DTMF_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Indicates whether the carrier supports the use of DTMF digits A-D for the purpose of device
     * to device communication while in a call.

variables.name: KEY_DISPLAY_HD_AUDIO_PROPERTY_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether High Definition audio property is displayed in the dialer UI.
     * If {@code false}, remove the HD audio property from the connection so that HD audio related
     * UI is not displayed. If {@code true}, keep HD audio property as it is configured.

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_IMS_CONFERENCE_CALL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether IMS conference calls are supported by a carrier. When {@code true},
     * IMS conference calling is supported, {@code false} otherwise.
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_LOCAL_DISCONNECT_EMPTY_IMS_CONFERENCE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether the device will locally disconnect an IMS conference when the participant * count drops to zero. When {@code true}, it is assumed the carrier does NOT disconnect a * conference when the participant count drops to zero and that the device must do this by * disconnecting the conference locally. When {@code false}, it is assumed that the carrier * is responsible for disconnecting the conference when there are no longer any participants * present. *

* Note: both {@link #KEY_SUPPORT_IMS_CONFERENCE_CALL_BOOL} and * {@link #KEY_SUPPORT_IMS_CONFERENCE_EVENT_PACKAGE_BOOL} must be true for this configuration to * have any effect. *

* Defaults to {@code false}, meaning the carrier network is responsible for disconnecting an * empty IMS conference. * @hide

variables.name: KEY_SUPPORT_VIDEO_CONFERENCE_CALL_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether video conference calls are supported by a carrier. When {@code true}, * video calls can be merged into conference calls, {@code false} otherwise. *

* Note: even if video conference calls are not supported, audio calls may be merged into a * conference if {@link #KEY_SUPPORT_CONFERENCE_CALL_BOOL} is {@code true}. * @hide

variables.name: KEY_EDITABLE_ENHANCED_4G_LTE_BOOL
variables.comment: * Determine whether user can toggle Enhanced 4G LTE Mode in Settings.

variables.name: KEY_HIDE_ENHANCED_4G_LTE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determines whether the Enhanced 4G LTE toggle will be shown in the settings. When this
     * option is {@code true}, the toggle will be hidden regardless of whether the device and
     * carrier supports 4G LTE or not.

variables.name: KEY_ENHANCED_4G_LTE_ON_BY_DEFAULT_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Sets the default state for the "Enhanced 4G LTE" or "Advanced Calling" mode toggle set by the
     * user. When this is {@code true}, this mode by default is on, otherwise if {@code false},
     * this mode by default is off.

variables.name: KEY_HIDE_IMS_APN_BOOL
variables.comment: * Determine whether IMS apn can be shown.

variables.name: KEY_HIDE_PREFERRED_NETWORK_TYPE_BOOL
variables.comment: * Determine whether preferred network type can be shown.

variables.name: KEY_ENABLE_APPS_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:
* String array for package names that need to be enabled for this carrier.
     * If user has explicitly disabled some packages in the list, won't re-enable.
     * Other carrier specific apps which are not in this list may be disabled for current carrier,
     * and only be re-enabled when this config for another carrier includes it.
     *
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_EDITABLE_WFC_MODE_BOOL
variables.comment:
* Determine whether user can switch Wi-Fi preferred or Cellular preferred
     * in calling preference.
     * Some operators support Wi-Fi Calling only, not VoLTE.
     * They don't need "Cellular preferred" option.
     * In this case, set uneditable attribute for preferred preference.

variables.name: KEY_CONFIG_WIFI_DISABLE_IN_ECBM
variables.comment: * Flag to indicate if Wi-Fi needs to be disabled in ECBM.

variables.name: KEY_WFC_OPERATOR_ERROR_CODES_STRING_ARRAY
variables.comment:

     * wfcOperatorErrorAlertMessages and wfcOperatorErrorNotificationMessages.
     *

     * used to find alert and notification messages in wfcOperatorErrorAlertMessages and
     * wfcOperatorErrorNotificationMessages.
     *
     * @hide

variables.name: KEY_WFC_SPN_FORMAT_IDX_INT
variables.comment:
* Indexes of SPN format strings in wfcSpnFormats. * *

Available options are: *

    *
  • 0: %s
    • *
  • 1: %s Wi-Fi Calling
    • *
  • 2: WLAN Call
    • *
  • 3: %s WLAN Call
    • *

variables.name: KEY_WFC_DATA_SPN_FORMAT_IDX_INT
variables.comment:
